OL,3,CPolice officer jailed for raping woman
OL,4,Cwhile off-duty
OL,6,F"I trusted him because he was a police
OL,7,Fofficer, but he broke the law, he
OL,8,Fraped, lied and treated me with such
OL,9,Fdisdain, being abusive and humiliating
OL,10,Fme whilst he laughed and thought it
OL,11,Fwas funny, laughing at my distress."
OL,13,FKelly Scrivener, defending, said Mines
OL,14,Fhad found in prison a difficult
OL,15,Fexperience because of his policing
OL,16,Fcareer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@dO]
